description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Educators Nursing Associates &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Corporate Nursing team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two Year fixed term contract or internal secondment / Substantive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a number of dynamic, self-motivated Band 6 Clinical Nurse Educators to work within University Hospitals Birmingham NHS Foundation Trust to provide clinical educational support to the Trainee Nursing Associate program across Good Hope Hospital, Solihull Hospital, Solihull Community Services, Heartlands Hospital and Queen Elizabeth Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dynamic, dedicated and enthusiastic individuals with the ability to enable and empower Trainee Nursing Associates within clinical environments and support mentors both in base clinical areas and in placement areas. As one of the clinical educators for the Trainee Nursing Associate programme you will need to provide assurance that standards of clinical education are met and sustained for the Trainee Nursing Associates through supporting them in practice to achieve their competences and meet the requirements of NMC regulation and post registration to meet their CPD requirements.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you have a minimum of 6 months experience at Band 6 and you can demonstrate effective management, leadership, teaching, communication and clinical skills we would like to hear from you. We are looking to expand the team of clinical educators as the numbers of trainees on program continue to grow. There are plans in 2020 to increase the numbers of TNA programmes and as such an opportunity has arisen to grow the clinical education team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details contact: Claire Whittle Lead Nurse Nursing Associates claire.whittle@heartofengland.nhs.uk or Rebecca Varney Educator Team Lead rebecca.varney@heartofengland.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date for applications&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;09th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
